{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.27",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 27,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 27 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:1",
      "text": "Boast not for to morrow, for thou knowest not what the day to come may bring forth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:2",
      "text": "Let another praise thee, and not thy own mouth: a stranger, and not thy own lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:3",
      "text": "A stone is heavy, and sand weighty: but the anger of a fool is heavier than them both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:4",
      "text": "Anger hath no mercy: nor fury, when it breaketh forth: and who can bear the violence of one provoked?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:5",
      "text": "Open rebuke is better than hidden love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:6",
      "text": "Better are the wounds of a friend, than the deceitful kisses of an enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:7",
      "text": "A soul that is full shall tread upon the honeycomb: and a soul that is hungry shall take even bitter for sweet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:8",
      "text": "As a bird that wandereth from her nest, so is a man that leaveth his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:9",
      "text": "Ointment and perfumes rejoice the heart: and the good counsels of a friend are sweet to the soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:10",
      "text": "Thy own friend, and thy father's friend, forsake not: and go not into thy brother's house in the day of thy affliction. Better is a neighbour that is near than a brother afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:11",
      "text": "Study wisdom, my son, and make my heart joyful, that thou mayst give an answer to him that reproacheth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:12",
      "text": "The prudent man seeing evil hideth himself: little ones passing on have suffered losses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:13",
      "text": "Take away his garment that hath been surety for a stranger: and take from him a pledge for strangers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:14",
      "text": "He that blesseth his neighbour with a loud voice, rising in the night, shall be like to him that curseth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:15",
      "text": "Roofs dropping through in a cold day, and a contentious woman are alike.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:16",
      "text": "He that retaineth her, is as he that would hold the wind, and shall call the oil of his right hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:17",
      "text": "Iron sharpeneth iron, so a man sharpeneth the countenance of his friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:18",
      "text": "He that keepeth the fig tree, shall eat the fruit thereof: and he that is the keeper of his master, shall be glorified.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:19",
      "text": "As the faces of them that look therein, shine in the water, so the hearts of men are laid open to the wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:20",
      "text": "Hell and destruction are never filled: so the eyes of men are never satisfied.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:21",
      "text": "As silver is tried in the fining-pot, and gold in the furnace: so a man is tried by the mouth of him that praiseth. The heart of the wicked seeketh after evils, but the righteous heart seeketh after knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:22",
      "text": "Though thou shouldst bray a fool in the mortar, as when a pestle striketh upon sodden barley, his folly would not be taken from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:23",
      "text": "Be diligent to know the countenance of thy cattle, and consider thy own flocks:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:24",
      "text": "For thou shalt not always have power: but a crown shall be given to generation and generation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:25",
      "text": "The meadows are open, and the green herbs have appeared, and the hay is gathered out of the mountains.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:26",
      "text": "Lambs are for thy clothing: and kids for the price of the field.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.27.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 27:27",
      "text": "Let the milk of the goats be enough for thy food, and for the necessities of thy house, and for maintenance for thy handmaids.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
